<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The conditional call to OS_FileSysFormatVolume_Impl(&token) is dead in this project: OS_FileSysFormatVolume_Impl is implemented as a no-op that always returns OS_SUCCESS, so executing it has no effect on program state or outputs. Removing the call (and associated assignment to return_code) would not change program behaviour (aside from negligible timing), therefore this constitutes dead code and violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2. (Note: if the implementation were to perform real formatting on some targets, the call would not be dead, but in the provided project it is.)
</scenario>

